‘A total of 1542 patients were randomized to Hydroxychloroquine and compared with 3132 patients randomized to usual care alone. There was no significant difference in the primary endpoint of 28-day mortality (25.7% Hydroxychloroquine vs. 23.5% usual care; hazard ratio 1.11 [95% confidence interval 0.98–1.26]; 
 p = 0.10). There was also no evidence of beneficial effects on hospital stay duration or other outcomes. Full results will be made available as soon as possible [
